// ext4recover.cpp
//
// Single-file Qt6 application (Widgets + WebEngine) that scans a device/image
// linearly for ext4 directory entries and shows a table with attributes:
//   Inode Nr. | Filename | Filesize | Create Date | Change Date
//
// Behavior summary
//  - Top: filesystem selector (mounted ext4 entries + "Select file..."), filter field
//  - Left: table with columns (Inode Nr., Filename, Filesize, Create Date, Change Date)
//  - Right: preview pane (QWebEngineView) for selected row
//  - Bottom: progress bar and ETA/status
//  - Scanner runs in a worker QThread and emits discovered placeholder paths of the form
//      "/[ino:<pseudo>]/<name>" and also emits the directory-entry inode number.
//  - When the selected device is mounted, the UI builds a map of inode -> file attributes
//    by walking the mountpoint (POSIX stat) and uses that to populate Filesize/Create/Change.
//  - If the device is not mounted, those fields remain empty (scanner still emits entries).
//
// Build (example):
//   mkdir build && cd build
//   cmake ..   (use a CMakeLists that finds Qt6 Widgets and WebEngineWidgets)
//   cmake --build .
//
// Notes:
//  - Scanning raw block devices usually requires root privileges. Use a disk image file
//    if you want to run as a normal user.
//  - This scanner reads direct blocks only (no extents/indirect). It is conservative
//    and emits placeholder-containing paths as requested. The UI resolves inode attributes
//    by traversing the mounted filesystem when available.
//
// Compile-time: requires Qt6 (Widgets + WebEngineWidgets).
//

